	<item>
		<title>Comment on A New Contract for America? by Anonymous</title>
		<link>http://werblog.com/2013/10/contract-for-america/#comment-2059</link>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Anonymous]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Sat, 04 Jan 2014 22:24:40 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://werblog.com/?p=5399#comment-2059</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[On a lot of the smaller news and opinion outlets, the leftists seem to be quite a bit in favour of reform, even if it tends to be the more blatant stuff like Citizens United.  The Democrats do have control right now, though, so the party itself would be losing ground by saying &quot;Hey, the government is messing up&quot; because when broken to soundbytes it would turn out to &quot;We suck&quot;. When the GOP reclaims the federal government, the Democrats could likely ramp up the support for reform.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>On a lot of the smaller news and opinion outlets, the leftists seem to be quite a bit in favour of reform, even if it tends to be the more blatant stuff like Citizens United.  The Democrats do have control right now, though, so the party itself would be losing ground by saying &#8220;Hey, the government is messing up&#8221; because when broken to soundbytes it would turn out to &#8220;We suck&#8221;. When the GOP reclaims the federal government, the Democrats could likely ramp up the support for reform.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
	</item>
